node.text: If every Monday was as consistently nice as her, we might all like them a little better! 😆 Mondays are always good days with Sister. 💪

node.text: Sister continued her near perfect streak on our route home, placing at Lawton and Sikeston! It was easy to get a little discouraged at the “rodeo hardships” we had where i thought we could’ve been faster and won them — bottom of the ground at one and a timer malfunction resulting in a hand flag at the other. But we’re home and i have a healthy and sound horse to be grateful for, and we’re enjoying peace and safety. People in Afghanistan can’t say the same right now. Silly me for getting wrapped up in my “problems”. Praying hard for the people there to find strength and safety. 🙏 #perspective #prayforafghanistan #prayforourcountry

node.text: Dodge City was a little wild but good to us! 😆 Sis was awesome in the first round winning 2nd, then while getting ready for our second round that night this sucker rolled in… so i got on old faithful TJ, and he was plenty fast enough to get us to the short round! A little slip in the short round cost us but we still ended up 3rd in the finals and 3rd in the average! Thankful for this pair 💛🖤 @_classicequine @cavenders @12gaugeranch @yeti @brazosvalleyequinehospitals @bloomertrailers @platinumperformance @purinaperformancehorse

location.name: Dodge City Roundup Rodeo "The Greatest Show on Dirt"

node.text:
Philipsburg, Kansas is a rodeo I’ve been excited to run Sis at! People ask, to an exhausting extent, why I’m not running her at every rodeo i show up to. I’m sure they think I’m leaving money on the table — sometimes i probably am. Maybe I’ve got other horses that need the run more. Maybe it’s the ground, or the lack of money to be won. Maybe, just maybe, she’s a horse, and she just needs a day. 
My ranching parents have taught me to be a good steward of what God gives us to care for. I don’t always nail it, but i pray every day for wisdom to be that for Sis, and for every horse, to never take them for granted. They’re not machines, not even Sister… and when she gets that day she wants or needs, she tells me thanks, in her own way, like this.
16.61 on a standard at Philipsburg for a new arena record and winning the rodeo with a couple perfs left.
She now unofficially holds the 3 fastest WPRA rodeo standard pattern runs: .56, .61, .63, all in the last year.

Thank you @ksbiggestrodeo for the exceptional ground prepped by Ricky Solida and for dragging after 6!
@_classicequine @yeti @bloomertrailers @12gaugeranch @purinaperformancehorse @platinumperformance @cavenders @brazosvalleyequinehospitals

Cheyenne Frontier Days champion feels amazing to say!! Sister is so fast, tough, honest and consistent with a never quit attitude, all of the things that rodeos like this make you value, so I’m so grateful to get this win for her. She deserves it! What a horse, what a blessing! Thank you @chefrontierdays for continuing the new standard in professional rodeo of dragging at the halfway mark in the finals for safety and fairness. Thank you Sis for giving me your whole heart every trip down that arena. ❤️❤️❤️ #thedaddyofemall #thankyouJesus

node.text:
Really fun run in our second round at Cheyenne! We’re moving onto the semi finals this weekend, thank you Sis 💛
@_classicequine @cavenders @yeti @12gaugeranch @brazosvalleyequinehospitals @bloomertrailers @platinumperformance @purinaperformancehorse

We love Ogden! Sister won this rodeo in 2019 and in 2020 they didn’t get to have their rodeo, so we were excited to go back this year and she got us another win! Big thank you to Johnny who works the ground in Ogden. He has improved the ground conditions over the years and this year it was not only safe but fair and consistent in each performance and slack. Johnny tries so hard to give us a great footing for our amazing animals, and i look forward to seeing more rodeos follow the example he sets in Ogden, Utah! @womensprofessionalrodeoassn @prca_prorodeo @cowboychannel 
@_classicequine @bloomertrailers @yeti @12gaugeranch @cavenders @brazosvalleyequinehospitals @platinumperformance @purinaperformancehorse

node.text:
One thing about rodeo, you don’t get to pick what the weather decides to do when you’re up… you only get to pick how much you smile about it! 😆🤷🏽‍♀️ And happily trot Nala through
Spanish Fork is one of our favorite rodeos with by far the best ground (barring a pre-rodeo rainstorm) and we look forward to it every year. We’ll be back next year and until then, we’re thankful Utah got some much needed rain! 🙏🙌🌧
